Description:
    Creates a new 'html' file.

Example:
    rails generate template buttons primary_buttons --type=component
        Where:
            'buttons' is the name of the category.
            'primary_buttons' is the name of template you want to create.
            --type=component saves the template as component in the db.

    rails generate template home_screens with_sidebar --type=page
        Where:
            'home_screens' is the name of the category.
            'with_sidebar' is the name of template you want to create.
            --type=page saves the template as page in the db.

    This will create:
        rails generate template buttons primary_buttons --type=component
            will create 'primary_buttons.html' file in 'buttons' directory.

        rails generate template home_screens with_sidebar --type=page
            will create 'with_sidebar.html' file in the 'home_screens' directory.
